---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Ed Barlow — Ed Barlow">
  <section class="home-intro">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h1 class="home-name">Ed Barlow</h1>
      <div class="home-body">
<h2><strong>AI Enabled Senior Principal Engineer / Technology Leader</strong> looking for <strong>AI Enablement Roles</strong> <br></h2>
<h2>My <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Process-Based-Database-Administration-Management-ebook/dp/B073RRQBZC">Process Based Methodology</a> and scale-proven <a href="https://webcloudstudio.github.io/webcloudstudio/project-docs/Specifications/Features.html">Technology Rules</a> combine into a <a href="https://webcloudstudio.github.io/webcloudstudio/project-docs/Specifications/white-paper.html">Specification Driven Framework</a></h2>
<p>This lets your programes seamlessly work together and gives you a unified <strong>command center</strong>.  </p>
<p>Tell claude to conform your existing projects and - it does it - minimal impact on your existing code.</p>
<p>Tell your AI agent <strong>to write a specification</strong> for the program you want to build not the program you want to build in a markdown.  Be clear it should provide no 'technical' details but should design a complete set of features and screens.  Put it in a directory and use our bash workflow to transform into a supportable application.  With complete control along the way so your application is what you want. </p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Control Panel</strong> - One View on all your projects (namespaced) with embedded Controls</li>
<li><strong>Service Catalog</strong> - provides Seamless Interoperability (Rest, CLI, Async interfaces)</li>
<li><strong>Opinionated Stack</strong> - Consistent Builds, Context Optimized </li>
<li><strong>Formal Workflow</strong> - Process Updating Applications, Light-weight kanban </li>
<li><strong>Seamless Operations</strong> - Monitoring, Documentation, Scheduled tasks, and Data Flows</li>
<li><strong>Self Iteration Workflow</strong> - Magically update your code with new features (you just ask it to)</li>
<li>Scorecards, Validators, and a Code Build Process <strong>ensure quality</strong></li>
<li><strong>Voice Control</strong> of your program fleet (in progress)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Principal Engineer/Director</strong> at hedge funds, investment banks, insurance companies, and startups </p>
<p><strong>Author</strong>, <strong>Speaker</strong>, <strong>Free Software Developer</strong></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .home-intro { padding: 4rem 0 3rem; }

    .home-name {
      font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin: 0 0 2rem;
    }

    .home-body { max-width: 860px; }

    .home-body p {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.75;
      margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    }

    .home-body h2 {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text);
      margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    }

    .home-body ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .home-body li {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      padding-left: 1.2rem;
      position: relative;
    }

    .home-body li::before {
      content: '—';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: var(--accent);
    }

    .home-body strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; }

    .home-body em {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 0.92rem;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
